@node Over "Overview"

@{b}Overview
--------@{ub}

These are the Amiga and Windows ports of Koules 1.4, a popular arcade
game for Linux and OS/2.

Features include: 1-5 players, sound, triple keyboard and quadruple
joystick/gamepad support, source code.
  The following features of the Linux and/or OS/2 versions are not
implemented in the Amiga and Windows versions:

    * network support
    * relative joystick support
    * user-selectable playfield size
    * 3D intros/outros
    * windowed mode (Amiga) and fullscreen mode (Windows)
    * analog joystick support (Amiga)

                                 -----
                                /     \\
                               | o | o |
===========================OO==============OO=============================

Koules is a fast action arcade-style game for UNIX, OS/2, AmigaOS 3,
AmigaOS 4, AROS, MorphOS and Windows. It has cool 256 color graphics,
multi-player mode up to 5 players and sound.
@endnode

@node Requ "System Requirements"

@{b}System Requirements
-------------------@{ub}

This is for the AmigaOS 3.x version of Koules:

@{b}Hardware@{ub}             Required        about 512K free RAM
                                     68020+
                                     AGA/RTG
                     Recommended     Joystick(s)
                                     CD32 controller(s)
                                     Flicker fixer
                                     RTG
                                     FPU
                                     OS4/MorphOS
                                     Sound card
                                     Mouse/trackball
@{b}Firmware@{ub}             Required        Kickstart 3.1+
@{b}Software@{ub}             Required        OS3.1+
                     Recommended     AHI

A reasonably fast Amiga is required to run the game at full speed. This
game runs *much* faster on an RTG screen than on an AGA screen, as it uses
chunky graphics.
  The AmigaOS 3 version uses Paula via the audio.device. If you remove the
#define USE_PAULA and recompile, you can use AHI sound instead.
  The AmigaOS 4 version uses AHI.
@endnode

@node Usag "Usage"

@{b}Usage
-----@{ub}

Koules can be run from the CLI or Workbench.
  No CLI arguments or Workbench ToolTypes are currently supported.
  Game settings are loaded/saved from/to the Koules.config file. To use a
different screenmode, quit to Workbench, delete Koules.config, and then
restart the game.
@endnode

