@node Play "How to Play"

@{b}Plot
----@{ub}

Somewhere in the galaxy...
  Once upon a time, the evil KOULES exhausted all the resources of their
home planet...
  Their emperor, THE DARK APPLEPOLISHER, deployed his brutal hyperspace
commandos to wipe out a human civilization and claim Earth's resources for
his realms...
  The nations of Earth chose their best warriors to defend our planet...
  These champions were biologically mutated into special creatures. Their
entities were reduced to mere chests and eyes...
  These qualities allow them operate in their enemies' domain...
  Your battle for a new world begins NOW...
  Your mission is to bounce all KOULES fighters from your sector...
  Some of them are deserters.
  The green ones give you acceleration.
  The blue ones give you more weight...
  Look out for mighty super-spherical megaheavy ultra green B_BALL...

@{b}Controls
--------@{ub}

    Left keyboard    Middle keyboard    Right keyboard

          W                 I                 Up
        A S D             J K L            Lt Dn Rt

Absolute: keys control facing direction and movement direction.
Relative: left/right rotate facing direction, up to move forwards.

For the Amiga version:
 Joystick '1' refers to the "mouse" port.
 Joystick '2' refers to the "joystick" port.
 Joystick '3' refers to the 1st parallel port joystick/gamepad.
 Joystick '4' refers to the 2nd parallel port joystick/gamepad.

Ctrl+X    toggles the mouse pointer on/off.
Ctrl+S    toggles the sound on/off.
Ctrl+B    toggles the "title bar" on/off (Amiga version only).
Esc       quits to the main menu.
Shift-Esc quits the program completely.

If you feel weak go away! I have to tell you a story about the stupidity
of your keyboard controller. Once upon a time IBM and Commodore made
stupid keyboards which are not able to handle more than 4 keys at a
time... [and less in some circumstances...]
  ...and they lived happily ever after.
@endnode

@node FAQs "Frequently Asked Questions"

@{b}Frequently Asked Questions
--------------------------@{ub}

[Q] - What is Koules?
[Q] - What does 'Koules' mean?
[Q] - Who makes Koules and how can I get in touch with them?
[Q] - Where can I obtain Koules?
[Q] - What is the latest version of Koules?
[Q] - Will Koules ever be ported to DOS?
[Q] - What are the point values?
[Q] - How many levels are in Koules?
[Q] - How much time will I need to complete Koules?
[Q] - Do you have any hints or tips for playing Koules?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
[Q] - What is Koules?

[A] - Koules is an arcade game for Unix/X11, linux/svgalib, OS/2, Amiga
      and Windows. It supports multi-player mode, high resolution,
      digitized sound, joysticks, up to 640x480 resolution with cool 256
      color graphics, 100 levels, etc.

      Koules is an original game. It was developed from scratch
      by Jan Hubicka in July 1995. It was ported to Windows in April
      2007, and to Amiga in February 2008, by James Jacobs of Amigan
      Software.

[Q] - What does 'Koules' mean?

[A] - Koules is an English plural of the Czech word 'koule' (= sphere).

[Q] - Who makes Koules and how can I get in touch with them?

[A] - Koules was published as freeware by Jan Hubicka.
      eMail: @{"hubicka@limax.paru.cas.cz" system "C:OpenURL mailto:hubicka@limax.paru.cas.cz"}

      It was ported to Amiga and Windows by James Jacobs of Amigan
      Software.
      eMail: @{"amigansoftware@gmail.com" system "C:OpenURL mailto:amigansoftware@gmail.com"}

[Q] - Where can I obtain Koules?

[A] - The latest version of Koules is always on the following sites:
      limax.paru.cas.cz:/pub/linux/games/koules
      sunsite.unc.edu  :/pub/linux/games/video
      tsx-11.mit.edu   :/pub/linux/sources/usr.games
                       :/pub/linux/binaries/usr.games
      @{"http://amigan.1emu.net/releases/" system "C:OpenURL http://amigan.1emu.net/releases/"}

[Q] - What is the latest version of Koules?

[A] - The current version of Koules is 1.4.

[Q] - Will Koules ever be ported to DOS?

[A] - No.

[Q] - What are the point values?

[A] - Bounce something           :    +1
      Eat extension              :   +10
      At end of level
       every life                :   +20
       every lost level          :  -100
      In deathmatch mode
       every destroyed competitor:  +100

[Q] - How many levels are in Koules?

[A] - 99 + 1 (bonus level :) ).

[Q] - How much time will I need to complete Koules?

[A] - stupid player:    a month
      worse player:     5 1/4 hours
      average player:   2 1/2 hours
      my friend and me: 50 minutes
      god:              1/1000000 ns

      (Medium difficulty)

[Q] - Do you have any hints or tips for playing Koules?

[A] - Standard KOULES fighters:
        - fly near borders (they may not be able to keep in the screen)
        - wait near the border, when they are near fly around them, and
          kick them out.
        - keep in the center
    - Standard B_BALLS:
        - hide behind holes
        - try to fly around magnetic holes (B_BALLS may fall into)
    - Inspectors:
        - wait behind them; B_BALLS will kick them out
@endnode
